I’ve been crushing on this chrome eyeshadow palette from ​⁠​⁠ the time I’ve gotten my hands on it . 
I have no complaints about it at all .
The pigmentation is beautiful 
The shine and the shift is great !
It’s so versatile I can use it for different clients in different ways 
They can layer well on different cream colours 
I even use them as highlighters sometimes 
The texture doesn’t feel chalky . 
There are so many colour options and some mattes as well . 
I did feel it was a huge amount for a palette but you actually end up getting quite a few colours which and the quality 🙌🏽! 

@zygosbeauty  This palette is stunning ✨🤌🏽🌸 . 
Love it , so much specially at work because I have so many options together at one place and I can switch it up as I like . 

You can use this technique and repeat this eye look in your own way . You can just add a black powder pigment instead of the purple and leave the chrome . 
You can use a different colour that you have instead of a purple .
You can also keep it as a brown to make it more subtle and tone it down . 
You can even switch out the shimmer chrome to another of your choice

Let me know if you try it out ! 🤎✨

I came across @asabeautyindia  when they sent over their products and I was extremely happy to see that they are an Indian brand who are > 92% natural in terms of their ingredients.
That took me to their website which has everything given in so much detail about what goes into their products and mainly what is consciously eliminated.
They are conscious not just about what goes into the products but about the environment too & that is why they have refills ( even for lipsticks) & minis! The packaging has a gorgeous minimal but classy aesthetic. 

I’m going to be honest I’ve been carrying the highlighter around in my bag since I got it.
I want to explore more of their products, especially the mascara, multi-face stick and blush! 

If you are mindful of the products that you are using on yourself do check them out. Or if you have tried them let me know in the comments which one is your favourite ✨🌸

“My definition of success keeps changing... As of now, it means to be able to genuinely enjoy my work,” says comedian Urooj Ashfaq (@uroojashfaq ). For her, getting behind the mic every single time, even on difficult days, is just as important. “Curiosity keeps me going despite all odds. If I’ve had a bad day, bad week, bad year. I’ll still ask, ‘What happens next? How does this turn out? How does this end?’”

Urooj Ashfaq has learnt much along the journey, and she is celebrating every step. “The greatest lesson I have learnt is being self-reliant. I am learning to really enjoy my own company, being satisfied with myself, and being kinder to and loving myself.”

#CelebrateEveryStep 

Urooj is wearing the Beige Bata Comfit sandals and Anessa shoes by NineWest at @bata.india , a velvet blazer by @suket.dhir , skirt by @akok.in , and jewellery by @karishma.joolry
